main event: A rapidly moving object was observed over the Pacific Ocean on December 14, 1963.
interesting points: The object was sighted by three observers who described it as having the brightness of a first magnitude star., The course of the object was towards the east., The length of the observation was 1 minute and 15 seconds., The altitude of the object could not be determined by the witnesses., The report was sent to several military and government branches for further analysis.
witness description: three observers with no specific data available
